# PWA / Vite env – copy to .env and set for real data.
# See web/README.md "Real data in the PWA" for details.
#   cp web/env.example web/.env
#
# Backend credentials: the PWA does not hold secrets. Start backend services (Alpaca, IB,
# Tastytrade, etc.) with credentials from env or 1Password (see docs/ONEPASSWORD_INTEGRATION.md),
# then point the PWA at them using VITE_API_URL and the port vars below.

# Snapshot / market data: prefer the shared Rust/nginx origin first.
# Unset = use static public/data/snapshot.json (offline).
# Preferred example:
#   Shared origin / Rust: http://localhost:8080/api/v1/snapshot
# Dev-only direct service examples:
#   IB:          http://127.0.0.1:8002/api/snapshot
#   Alpaca:      http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/snapshot
#   Tastytrade:  http://127.0.0.1:8005/api/snapshot
# When set, the web app also derives unified health from the same origin: {base}/api/health-aggregated.
# VITE_API_URL=

# Optional: unified health dashboard URL. If set, header status uses one request here instead of per-service.
# When using nginx at 8080, prefer setting VITE_API_URL above; otherwise point at the dashboard directly, e.g.:
# VITE_HEALTH_AGGREGATED_URL=http://localhost:8011/api/health
# VITE_HEALTH_AGGREGATED_URL=

# Optional archived-web shared config URL. Prefer Rust/shared origin when used:
# VITE_CONFIG_URL=http://localhost:8080/api/config

# Rust backend (box spread scenarios, charts, cash flow, opportunity simulation).
# VITE_RUST_BACKEND_REST_PORT=8080

# Optional dev overrides: direct service ports when not using the shared origin.
# VITE_IB_PORT=8002
# VITE_ALPACA_PORT=8000
# VITE_TASTYTRADE_PORT=8005
# VITE_DISCOUNT_BANK_PORT=8003
# VITE_RISK_FREE_RATE_PORT=8004

# Optional: IB Gateway / Client Portal URL for "Open IB Gateway" link in PWA header (default: https://localhost:5001).
# VITE_IB_GATEWAY_URL=https://localhost:5001

# Optional: use LEAN API for snapshot/strategy instead of VITE_API_URL.
# VITE_USE_LEAN_API=false
# VITE_LEAN_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
